Fernando Climent Huerta (born May 27, 1958 in Coria del Ro, Sevilla) is a retired competition rower and Olympic champion from Spain. He won a silver medal in coxless pairs at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles, together with Luis Mara Lasrtegui.[1] Nowadays is the President of the Spanish Rowing Federation. http://www.federemo.org 
